The group $G\rtimes_{\psi} H$ is called the \textbf{$\psi$-compression factor}. Normal compression maps factor through this group.

\begin{thm}[\cite{RW_P_15} Theorem~3.6]\label{thm:psi-compression_factor_rel}
Let $G$ and $H$ be Polish groups with $\psi: G \rightarrow H$ a normal compression map and let $O\leq H$ be an open subgroup. Then the following hold:
