One naturally asks for which groups is ${\mathfrak{{B}}}_G^r$ non-empty. We now see that compactly generated \lcsc groups without robustly non-negligible chief blocks have a very restricted structure. In later work, we will prove analogues of these results for all  \lcsc groups.

